				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">MottZilla wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Another I think would be cool would be extra RAM - 8KB (0000 to 1FFF rather than mirrored 0000 to 07FF), support for a higher CPU clock speed, support for some kind of DMA to the PPU for fast name table and pattern table updates, extra sound hardware.</div>
<br />So it appears  you'd like these specs:
<br /><ul><li>8 KiB of main RAM </li><li>120 KiB of extra RAM </li><li>2.7 MHz CPU </li><li>16-bit arithmetic instructions </li><li>16-bit base pointer for accessing all of main RAM with zero page instructions </li><li>16-bit stack pointer </li><li>32 KiB bankswitching with hardware support for calls to subroutines in other banks </li><li>16 palettes, each with 16 colors </li><li>DMA for fast copies to VRAM </li><li>DMA channels for automatic raster effects </li><li>2 background planes </li><li>Bigger sprites, and more of them </li><li>DPCM-on-steroids sampled audio playback chip with its own dedicated CPU and 64 KiB of RAM </li></ul>
<br />In other words, you want a "super" NES.</div>

